          Jun 28, 2017                         - RelSci Data Update                

          Institutional Holdings Changes      




Background Information:


Aurelius Capital Management LP »
Aurelius Capital Management's (ACM) funds seek to maximize returns while preserving capital and minimizing correlation with the overall financial markets. The funds are generally referred to as distressed credit and event driven funds. The funds' investments may be concentrated in one or more of the following categories: entities that are, or face the prospect of becoming, financially stressed or distressed; entities undergoing, or facing the prospect of undergoing, significant corporate events; investments that may be affected by material legal disputes; companies facing material regulatory developments; and capital structure arbitrage. The funds may invest in all manner of instruments and obligations, including equity and debt securities, bank debt, trade debt, options, contractual and litigation claims, market and sector indices and derivatives. The funds may invest anywhere in the world, but ACM has a strong preference for countries having reliable legal systems and markets.




